Ernesto Duarte Brito (Jovellanos (Cuba), November 7, 1922 – Madrid, Spain, March 4, 1988) was a Cuban musician, author of the bolero Cómo fue, whose performance by Benny Moré became very famous.
He left Cuba in 1961 to settle in Madrid, Spain, where he died on March 4, 1988, at the age of 65.
